SIMPLE: thumbscrew
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thumbscrew
<hw>Thumb"screw`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
screw having a flat-sided or knurled head, so that it may be turned by
the thumb and forefinger.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An old instrument of torture for compressing the
thumb by a screw; a thumbkin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thummie</ent>⟦br⟧
